//
// test/sema/width/unary_expr.test — unary-operator width fixture
// (T024 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a). Per N2
// (lang.ebnf:1023), unary `~`, `!`, and reduction `&`/`|`/`^` apply
// to a single operand. Asserts the resulting `UnaryExpr` carries a
// `: BitVector(N)` Type suffix per `emit-ast-format.contract.md`
// Invariant 2.

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  wire a;\n  reg b = ~a;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (ModuleBlock {{.*}}name=m
// CHECK: (RegDecl {{.*}}name=b
// CHECK: (UnaryExpr {{.*}} : BitVector({{[0-9]+}})
